Name: prince_william_2009_rpa
LayerDisplayName: Resource Protection Areas, Prince William County, VA
Originator: Prince William County Office of Information Technology
OriginatorSort: Prince William County Office of Information Technology
Abstract: This polygon represents the approximate locations of Resource Protection Areas located within Prince William County, VA. RPA's include the land area within 100 feet of a perennial stream bank or edge of wetlands adjacent to the perennial stream. RPA areas are protected under state law and local ordinances. In general, no development, land disturbance, or vegetation removal is allowed in an RPA. RPA's were designated along all perennial streams in the County.

    <descript>
      <abstract>This polygon represents the approximate locations of Resource Protection Areas located within Prince William County, VA. RPA's include the land area within 100 feet of a perennial stream bank or edge of wetlands adjacent to the perennial stream. RPA areas are protected under state law and local ordinances. In general, no development, land disturbance, or vegetation removal is allowed in an RPA. RPA's were designated along all perennial streams in the County.</abstract>
      <purpose>This dataset is intended for researchers, students, and policy makers for reference and mapping purposes, and may be used for basic applications such as viewing, querying, and map output production, or to provide a base map to support graphical overlays and analysis with other spatial data. </purpose>
